{"parse":{"title":"Bertram D. Lewin","pageid":50590265,"revid":841136241,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p><p><b>Bertram D. Lewin</b> (Bertram David, 1896-1971) was an American <a href=\"/wiki/Psychoanalyst\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Psychoanalyst\">psychoanalyst</a> who was both an acute clinician and a contributor to theory, particularly to the study of <a href=\"/wiki/Hypermania\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hypermania\">elation</a>, and of the dream screen.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Training_and_contributions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Training and contributions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Selected_publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Training_and_contributions\">Training and contributions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bertram_D._Lewin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Training and contributions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lewin had a training analysis with <a href=\"/wiki/Franz_Alexander\" title=\"Franz Alexander\">Franz Alexander</a> in Berlin in the twenties, before publishing his first analytic article in 1930.  This was followed by ten more over the next decade, on subjects ranging from diabetes and <a href=\"/wiki/Claustrophobia\" title=\"Claustrophobia\">claustrophobia</a> to the body as <a href=\"/wiki/Phallus\" title=\"Phallus\">phallus</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  The main focus of his interest, however, was in manic states, which he saw as characterised by fleeting identifications with a multiple of outside figures.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the war, he published the fruits of his investigations in <i>The Psychoanalysis of Elation</i> (1951).  There he stressed the role of <a href=\"/wiki/Denial\" title=\"Denial\">denial</a> in mania \u2013 denial particularly of feelings of separation and loss.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  He also explored the paradox in elation's dark counterpart, depression, whereby the melancholic in seeking to punish the effigy of their loved one in fact punishes themselves having incorporated this effigy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>By that point he had also published his seminal article (1946) on the dream screen \u2013 the backcloth formed from primitive memories of the breast onto which the dream is projected.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  The concept would be fruitfully followed up both within analysis,<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and in the context of <a href=\"/wiki/Film_theory\" title=\"Film theory\">film theory</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_publications\">Selected publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bertram_D._Lewin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>____<i>The Image and the Past</i> (1968)\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bertram_D._Lewin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"div-col columns column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 22em; -webkit-column-width: 22em; column-width: 22em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Apparatus_theory\" title=\"Apparatus theory\">Apparatus theory</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Benjamin_Spock\" title=\"Benjamin Spock\">Benjamin Spock</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gregory_Zilboorg\" title=\"Gregory Zilboorg\">Gregory Zilboorg</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Oneiric_(film_theory)\" title=\"Oneiric (film theory)\">Oneiric (film theory)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sigmund_Freud_Archives\" title=\"Sigmund Freud Archives\">Sigmund Freud Archives</a></li></ul></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bertram_D._Lewin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li i